res exceeding 34C and humidity reaching nearly 70%.\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3330}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3378}, {\"ngram\": \"temperatures\", \"from\": 3386, \"to\": 3398}, {\"ngram\": \"humidity\", \"from\": 3417, \"to\": 3425}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly 70%\", \"from\": 3435, \"to\": 3445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking about those Games, Marcus Daniell, aNew Zealandtennis player and Olympic bronze medallist, said: \\\"I felt like the heat was bordering on true risk - the type of risk that could potentially be fatal.\\\"\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3476, \"end\": 3482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\", \"score\": 0.9998605304560525, \"rank\": 0.00013948899841785932, \"text\": \"Marcus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those Games\", \"from\": 3463, \"to\": 3474}, {\"ngram\": \"aNew Zealandtennis player\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3517}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic bronze medallist\", \"from\": 3522, \"to\": 3546}, {\"ngram\": \"the heat\", \"from\": 3567, \"to\": 3575}, {\"ngram\": \"true risk\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3602}, {\"ngram\": \"the type\", \"from\": 3605, \"to\": 3613}, {\"ngram\": \"risk\", \"from\": 3617, \"to\": 3621}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, Pragnya Mohan, the highest-ranking triathlete in Indian history, said she can no longer train in her home country because of the heat.\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3668, \"end\": 3681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pragnya_Mohan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999131433, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pragnya Mohan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pragnya_Mohan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pragnya_Mohan\"}, {\"begin\": 3717, \"end\": 3731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_India\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Indian history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the highest-ranking triathlete\", \"from\": 3683, \"to\": 3713}, {\"ngram\": \"her home country\", \"from\": 3765, \"to\": 3781}, {\"ngram\": \"the heat\", \"from\": 3793, \"to\": 3801}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She added that sponsors want \\\"more visibility\\\" so events tend to be held in the afternoons for maximum public turnout, meaning she has competed in \\\"extremely dangerous\\\" conditions with 40C-plus temperatures and humidity was 80%-plus.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 4037, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sponsors\", \"from\": 3819, \"to\": 3827}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"more visibility\", \"from\": 3833, \"to\": 3849}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 3854, \"to\": 3860}, {\"ngram\": \"the afternoons\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3894}, {\"ngram\": \"maximum public turnout\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 3921}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"extremely dangerous\\\" conditions\", \"from\": 3951, \"to\": 3983}, {\"ngram\": \"40C-plus temperatures\", \"from\": 3989, \"to\": 4010}, {\"ngram\": \"humidity\", \"from\": 4015, \"to\": 4023}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The report produced by the British Association for Sustainable Sport and FrontRunners outlined five recommendations to better support and protect athletes from extreme heat.\", \"from\": 4039, \"to\": 4212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4112, \"end\": 4124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FrontRunners\", \"score\": 0.669467902590356, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FrontRunners\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FrontRunners\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FrontRunners\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The report\", \"from\": 4039, \"to\": 4049}, {\"ngram\": \"the British Association\", \"from\": 4062, \"to\": 4085}, {\"ngram\": \"Sustainable Sport\", \"from\": 4090, \"to\": 4107}, {\"ngram\": \"five recommendations\", \"from\": 4134, \"to\": 4154}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4185, \"to\": 4193}, {\"ngram\": \"extreme heat\", \"from\": 4199, \"to\": 4211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With global temperatures continuing to rise, climate change should increasingly be viewed as an existential threat to sport Alongside smarter scheduling to avoid heat extremes, these were urging sporting authorities to introduce better rehydration and cooling plans for athletes, empowering athletes to speak out on climate change, boosting collaboration between sporting bodies and athletes on climate awareness campaigns, and reassessing fossil fuel sponsorship in sport.\", \"from\": 4214, \"to\": 4688, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"global temperatures\", \"from\": 4219, \"to\": 4238}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 4259, \"to\": 4273}, {\"ngram\": \"an existential threat\", \"from\": 4307, \"to\": 4328}, {\"ngram\": \"smarter scheduling\", \"from\": 4348, \"to\": 4366}, {\"ngram\": \"heat extremes\", \"from\": 4376, \"to\": 4389}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting authorities\", \"from\": 4409, \"to\": 4429}, {\"ngram\": \"better rehydration\", \"from\": 4443, \"to\": 4461}, {\"ngram\": \"plans\", \"from\": 4474, \"to\": 4479}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4484, \"to\": 4492}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4505, \"to\": 4513}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 4530, \"to\": 4544}, {\"ngram\": \"collaboration\", \"from\": 4555, \"to\": 4568}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting bodies\", \"from\": 4577, \"to\": 4592}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4597, \"to\": 4605}, {\"ngram\": \"climate awareness campaigns\", \"from\": 4609, \"to\": 4636}, {\"ngram\": \"fossil fuel sponsorship\", \"from\": 4654, \"to\": 4677}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 4681, \"to\": 4686}]}, {\"sentence\": \"LordSebastian Coe, president of World Athletics and four-time Olympic medallist, said: \\\"For athletes, from smaller performance-impacting issues like sleep disruption and last-minute changes to event timings, to exacerbated health impacts and heat-related stress and injury, the consequences can be varied and wide-ranging.\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 5012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4722, \"end\": 4737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999974493221, \"rank\": 2.5507591697974915e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"LordSebastian Coe\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 4707}, {\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 4709, \"to\": 4718}, {\"ngram\": \"four-time Olympic medallist\", \"from\": 4742, \"to\": 4769}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4782, \"to\": 4790}, {\"ngram\": \"smaller performance-impacting issues\", \"from\": 4797, \"to\": 4833}, {\"ngram\": \"sleep disruption\", \"from\": 4839, \"to\": 4855}, {\"ngram\": \"last-minute changes\", \"from\": 4860, \"to\": 4879}, {\"ngram\": \"event timings\", \"from\": 4883, \"to\": 4896}, {\"ngram\": \"health impacts\", \"from\": 4913, \"to\": 4927}, {\"ngram\": \"heat-related stress\", \"from\": 4932, \"to\": 4951}, {\"ngram\": \"injury\", \"from\": 4956, \"to\": 4962}, {\"ngram\": \"the consequences\", \"from\": 4964, \"to\": 4980}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With global temperatures continuing to rise, climate change should increasingly be viewed as an existential threat to sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 5014, \"to\": 5140, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"global temperatures\", \"from\": 5020, \"to\": 5039}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 5060, \"to\": 5074}, {\"ngram\": \"an existential threat\", \"from\": 5108, \"to\": 5129}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 5133, \"to\": 5138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other athletes involved in the report were Hannah Mills, British Olympic sailing champion, Imogen Grant, British Olympic rower, Eliza McCartney, a New Zealand bronze Olympic medallist in pole vault, Kelsey-Lee Barber, Australian Olympic bronze medallist in javelin, Rhydian Cowley, an Australian Olympic racewalker, Ajla Del Ponte, a Swiss Olympic springer, Elena Vallortigara, Italian high jump Olympian, Morten Thorsby, a Norwegian footballer, Jenny Casson, a Canadian Olympic rower, and Katie Rood, a New Zealand football player.\", \"from\": 5142, \"to\": 5674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5185, \"end\": 5197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mills\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3657380376559308e-22, \"text\": \"Hannah Mills\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mills\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mills\"}, {\"begin\": 5199, \"end\": 5206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999814030016361, \"rank\": 0.0001843053297931648, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 5233, \"end\": 5245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imogen_Grant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imogen Grant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imogen_Grant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imogen_Grant\"}, {\"begin\": 5247, \"end\": 5254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999814030016361, \"rank\": 0.0001843053297931648, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 5270, \"end\": 5285,